Revision history for Kubernetes-REST

{{$NEXT}}
 - Complete rewrite for v1 API
 - Now uses IO::K8s for Kubernetes resource classes
 - Simplified API: list(), get(), create(), update(), patch(), delete()
 - Patch API support: patch() for partial updates with strategic-merge-patch, merge-patch,
   and json-patch
 - Watch API support: watch() for streaming resource changes via Kubernetes Watch API
 - Kubernetes::REST::WatchEvent class for typed watch events
 - Resumable watches via resourceVersion tracking
 - Label and field selector support for watch()
 - Automatic URL building from IO::K8s class metadata
 - Custom Resource Definition (CRD) support: use your own CRD classes with the standard API
 - _build_path supports resource_plural from CRD classes for custom plural names
 - Backwards compatibility via deprecated v0 API wrappers (Apps->ListNamespacedPod, etc)
 - Resource map for short class names (Pod -> Core::V1::Pod)
 - Resource map '+' prefix for external classes ('+My::CRD' uses class as-is)
 - Dynamic resource map loading from cluster (/openapi/v2)
 - Deprecation stubs for removed classes (backwards compatibility)
 - New kube_watch CLI tool for watching Kubernetes resource events
 - Comprehensive documentation and examples in Kubernetes::REST::Example
 - Updated maintainer to GETTY

All pre-v1 releases by Jose Luis Martinez Torres (JLMARTIN)

0.02     2019-02-11 00:00:00Z
 - Fix all calls that have a body parameter: Create*, Patch*, Replace*, etc..

0.01     2019-01-03 00:00:00Z
 - First release into an unsuspecting world
